### Question 5: Compaction

Total memory used by processes = $3000 + 2000 + 4000 + 2000 + 5000 = 16,000$ bytes.
Total memory = $30,000$ bytes.
Free memory = $30,000 - 16,000 = 14,000$ bytes.

The instructions state that all free memory should coalesce to **begin at address 0**. This means the 14,000 bytes of free memory will occupy addresses $0$ to $13,999$. The processes will then be relocated starting at address $14,000$.

| Process | BASE Register | LIMIT Register |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| Process 0 | 14,000 | 3000 |
| Process 1 | 17,000 | 2000 |
| Process 2 | 19,000 | 4000 |
| Process 3 | 23,000 | 2000 |
| Process 4 | 25,000 | 5000 |

